          "author": {
            "login": "ConcaveTrillion"
          },
          "body": "**Context:** Found while building Tier-B real-OCR e2e in `pdomain-ocr-simple-gui` (behavior-e2e-pilot M2).\n\nThe `det_bs` / `reco_bs` kwargs on `get_finetuned_torch_doctr_predictor` are committed (`5585d27`) but **untagged / unreleased**. Editable `pdomain-ops` (`gpu/local_stage.py`) already calls them, so any registry-pinned consumer fails real OCR:\n\n```\nTypeError: get_finetuned_torch_doctr_predictor() got an unexpected keyword argument 'det_bs'\n```\n\n`pdomain-ocr-simple-gui` pins `pdomain-book-tools>=0.14.1` → resolves `0.14.2`, which lacks these kwargs. Tier-B real OCR only passes with the editable sibling (`0.14.3.dev12`).\n\n**Ask:** Cut a release carrying `5585d27` so downstream consumers can bump their pin and run real OCR from the registry path.",
          "closedAt": null,
          "comments": {
            "nodes": []
          },
          "createdAt": "2026-05-29T17:15:24Z",
